channel.title: CVE Feed for IBM -- QRadar SIEM
channel.description: The latest CVEs for IBM -- QRadar SIEM

item.title: CVE-2020-4993|2024-08-04T08:22:08.474Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 when decompressing or verifying signature of zip files processes data in a way that may be vulnerable to path traversal attacks. IBM X-Force ID: 192905.

item.title: CVE-2020-4932|2024-08-04T08:14:59.184Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 contains hard-coded credentials, such as a password or cryptographic key, which it uses for its own inbound authentication, outbound communication to external components, or encryption of internal data. IBM X-Force ID: 191748.

item.title: CVE-2021-38869|2024-08-04T01:51:20.504Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3, 7.4, and 7.5 in some situations may not automatically log users out after they exceede their idle timeout. IBM X-Force ID: 208341.

item.title: CVE-2020-4280|2024-08-04T08:00:07.098Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by insecure deserialization of user-supplied content by the Java deserialization function. By sending a malicious serialized Java object, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system. IBM X-Force ID: 176140.

item.title: CVE-2021-38939|2024-08-04T01:51:20.603Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3, 7.4, and 7.5 stores potentially sensitive information in log files that could be read by an user with access to creating domains. IBM X-Force ID: 211037.

item.title: CVE-2020-4979|2024-08-04T08:22:08.530Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 is vulnerable to insecure inter-deployment communication. An attacker that is able to comprimise or spoof traffic between hosts may be able to execute arbitrary commands. IBM X-Force D: 192538.

item.title: CVE-2020-4512|2024-08-04T08:07:48.922Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 could allow a remote privileged user to execute commands.

item.title: CVE-2020-4883|2024-08-04T08:14:59.089Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 could disclose sensitive information about other domains which could be used in further attacks against the system. IBM X-Force ID: 190907.

item.title: CVE-2020-4929|2024-08-04T08:14:59.109Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 is vulnerable to cross-site scripting. This vulnerability allows users to embed arbitrary JavaScript code in the Web UI thus altering the intended functionality potentially leading to credentials disclosure within a trusted session. IBM X-Force ID: 191706.

item.title: CVE-2020-4510|2024-08-04T08:07:48.877Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 is vulnerable to an XML External Entity Injection (XXE) attack when processing XML data. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to expose sensitive information or consume memory resources. IBM X-Force ID: 182365.

item.title: CVE-2020-5013|2024-08-04T08:22:08.469Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 may vulnerable to a XML External Entity Injection (XXE) attack when processing XML data. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to expose sensitive information or consume memory resources. IBM X-Force ID: 193245.

item.title: CVE-2020-5032|2024-08-04T08:22:09.003Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 in some configurations may be vulnerable to a temporary denial of service attack when sent particular payloads. IBM X-Force ID: 194178.

item.title: CVE-2021-39088|2024-08-04T01:58:17.738Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3, 7.4, and 7.5 is vulnerable to local privilege escalation if this could be combined with other unknown vulnerabilities then privilege escalation could be performed. IBM X-Force ID: 216111.

item.title: CVE-2020-4151|2024-08-04T08:00:07.348Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3.0 through 7.3.3 could allow an authenticated attacker to perform unauthorized actions due to improper input validation. IBM X-Force ID: 174201.

item.title: CVE-2020-4888|2024-08-04T08:14:59.135Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.4.0 to 7.4.2 Patch 1 and 7.3.0 to 7.3.3 Patch 7 could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by insecure deserialization of user-supplied content by the Java deserialization function. By sending a malicious serialized Java object, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system. IBM X-Force ID: 190912.

item.title: CVE-2021-38936|2024-08-04T01:51:20.764Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3, 7.4, and 7.5 could disclose highly sensitive information to a privileged user. IBM X-Force ID: 210893.

item.title: CVE-2020-4787|2024-08-04T08:14:58.604Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.4.2 GA to 7.4.2 Patch 1, 7.4.0 to 7.4.1 Patch 1, and 7.3.0 to 7.3.3 Patch 5 is vulnerable to server side request forgery (SSRF). This may allow an authenticated attacker to send unauthorized requests from the system, potentially leading to network enumeration or facilitating other attacks. IBM X-Force ID: 189224.

item.title: CVE-2021-39041|2024-08-04T01:58:17.283Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3, 7.4, and 7.5 may be vulnerable to partial denial of service attack, resulting in some protocols not listening to specified ports. IBM X-Force ID: 214028.

item.title: CVE-2021-38919|2024-08-04T01:51:20.865Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3, 7.4, and 7.5 in some senarios may reveal authorized service tokens to other QRadar users. IBM X-Force ID: 210021

item.title: CVE-2020-4786|2024-08-04T08:14:58.379Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.4.2 GA to 7.4.2 Patch 1, 7.4.0 to 7.4.1 Patch 1, and 7.3.0 to 7.3.3 Patch 5 is vulnerable to server side request forgery (SSRF). This may allow an authenticated attacker to send unauthorized requests from the system, potentially leading to network enumeration or facilitating other attacks. IBM X-Force ID: 189221.

item.title: CVE-2021-38874|2024-08-04T01:51:20.371Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3, 7.4, and 7.5 allows for users to access information across tenant and domain boundaries in some situations. IBM X-Force ID: 208397.

item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 is vulnerable to an XML External Entity Injection (XXE) attack when processing XML data. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to expose sensitive information or consume memory resources. IBM X-Force ID: 182364.

item.title: CVE-2021-38878|2024-08-04T01:51:20.452Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar 7.3, 7.4, and 7.5 could allow a malicious actor to impersonate an actor due to key exchange without entity authentication. IBM X-Force ID: 208756.

item.title: CVE-2020-4364|2024-08-04T08:00:07.130Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 is vulnerable to cross-site scripting. This vulnerability allows users to embed arbitrary JavaScript code in the Web UI thus altering the intended functionality potentially leading to credentials disclosure within a trusted session. IBM X-Force ID: 178961.

item.title: CVE-2020-4511|2024-08-04T08:07:49.000Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 could allow an authenticated user to cause a denial of service of the qflow process by sending a malformed sflow command. IBM X-Force ID: 182366.

item.title: CVE-2020-4789|2024-08-04T08:14:58.453Z -- ibm -- qradar%20siem
item.description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.4.2 GA to 7.4.2 Patch 1, 7.4.0 to 7.4.1 Patch 1, and 7.3.0 to 7.3.3 Patch 5 could allow a remote attacker to traverse directories on the system. An attacker could send a specially-crafted URL request containing "dot dot" sequences (/../) to view arbitrary files on the system. IBM X-Force ID: 189302.
